proxySettingsManager.loadFromPreferences { (error) in
    guard error == nil else {
        print("Error loading proxy settings: \(error!)")
        return
    }
    proxySettingsManager.setOnDemandEnabled(false)
    proxySettingsManager.setProxySettings(proxySettings) { (error) in
        guard error == nil else {
            print("Error setting proxy settings: \(error!)")
            return
        }
        print("Proxy settings successfully set.")
    }
}
```

This code disables the automatic proxy configuration (PAC) file and sets the HTTP proxy server and port to `proxy.example.com` and `8080`, respectively. You can adjust these values to match your specific proxy settings. Once these settings are applied, all HTTP connections on the Wi-Fi network will use the specified proxy. Note that this code requires the `NetworkExtension` framework to be imported at the beginning of your Swift file.

